ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: What are you most worried about in your life at the moment?
How much has it affected you over the last week?
Notes: 0=Not at all; 1=A little; 2= Somewhat; 3=Quite a lot; 4=Very much; -888= missing

ElementDescription: How long ago were you first worried about this problem?
Notes: 1=Just this week; 2= Last term; 3=Last year; 4=Longer than that; -888= missing

ElementDescription: Is there something that's hard to do because of this problem?
How hard has it been to do this thing over the last week?
Notes: 0=Not at all hard; 1=A little hard; 2=Somewhat hard; 3= Quite hard; 4=Very hard; -888= missing

ElementDescription: How do you feel about going to therapy?/If someone helps with you with this problem, how would you feel?
How have you felt this last week?
If you had 3 wishes to help you what would they be?
